rules: Rule1: Either the agent needs cover or the agent creates a distraction.
Rule2: Under the condition that the agent creates a distraction, the agent destroys evidence.
Rule3: If the agent is under surveillance, then if the agent needs cover, the agent uses encryption.
Rule4: The agent is under surveillance or the agent suspects compromise.
Rule5: If the agent suspects compromise, then whenever the agent needs cover, the agent uses encryption.
Rule6: If the agent confirms their identity, then the agent's mission is successful.
Rule7: If the agent is a member of the rival organization, then under the condition that the agent has access to office furniture, the agent's mission is successful.
Rule8: If the agent aborts the mission, then the agent calls backup.
Rule9: If the agent has an opportunity, then whenever the agent plants a device, the agent accesses the server.
Rule10: If the agent retrieves data, then the agent's mission is successful.
Rule11: If the agent locates the target, then under the condition that the agent has access to office furniture, the agent retrieves data.
Rule12: If the agent identifies the target, then the agent locates the target.
Rule13: If the agent uses a decoy, then it is not the case that the agent intercepts a message.
Rule14: If the agent goes dark, then the agent does not intercept a message.
Rule15: If the agent steals data containing vehicle specifications, then the agent plants a device.
Rule16: If the agent executes a protocol, then either the agent changes their identity or the agent does not maintain cover.
Rule17: If the agent has authorized access to office furniture, then the agent does not steal data containing vehicle specifications.
Rule18: If the agent receives a signal, then the agent's mission is successful.
Rule19: If the agent intercepts a message, then the agent gets caught.
Rule20: Either the agent intercepts a message or the agent receives a signal.
Rule21: If the agent uses encryption, then the agent does not get caught.
Rule22: If the agent destroys evidence, then the agent does not get caught.
Rule23: If it is not the case that either the agent reveals their identity or the agent confirms their identity, then the agent activates extraction.
Rule24: If it is not the case that if the agent detects a threat then under the condition that the agent activates extraction the agent escapes safely, then the agent aborts the mission.
Rule25: If it is not the case that if the agent detects a threat then provided that the agent activates extraction the agent escapes safely, then the agent does not call backup.
Rule26: If it is not the case that either the agent uses a decoy or the agent goes dark, then the agent maintains cover.
Rule27: If the agent is not a member of the rival organization, then the agent steals data containing vehicle specifications.
facts: Fact1: The agent has access to office furniture.
Fact2: The agent detects a threat.
Fact3: The agent has an opportunity.
Fact4: The agent identifies the target.
Fact5: The agent executes a protocol.
Fact6: The agent has authorized access to office furniture.
Fact7: It is not the case that the agent reveals their identity.
Fact8: The agent does not escape safely.
Fact9: The agent does not access the server.
Fact10: The agent does not change their identity.
